---
description: Building decks and reading validation output
globs:
  - "src/deckstudio/**"
  - "decks/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

Build loop:
1. `deckstudio validate <deck>` — schema errors name the slide id and field,
   and say what to do; fix the spec, not the schema.
2. `deckstudio build <deck>` — writes `output/<name>_vN.pptx`. Versions
   auto-increment and old versions are NEVER overwritten (Joe may have
   hand-edited them). `build_log.md` in the deck folder maps versions to
   repo state.
3. Build warnings (e.g. missing icon asset, animation skipped) are printed —
   relay anything Joe would care about.
4. If the post-build smoke-check fails, it's an ENGINE bug (slide/chart count
   mismatch, chart without embedded workbook). Report it; never work around
   it by changing the spec.
5. Optional visual check: `deckstudio build <deck> --preview` renders PNGs
   via LibreOffice if installed; absence is fine, not an error.

Charts are native PowerPoint charts with embedded editable data — that is a
guarantee this repo makes. Anything that would replace a chart with an image
is wrong.

`deckstudio doctor` diagnoses environment problems (missing fonts, template,
logo assets).
